1 -> Make sure you have Node.js and MongoDB installed on your machine.
Create a new directory for your project and navigate to it in the terminal:

code = mkdir hospital-management-system
code = cd hospital-management-system

2 -> Initialize your Node.js project:

copy = npm init -y

3 -> Install the required packages:

copy = npm install express mongoose body-parser ejs

<paste the app.js in file and add another file in vs code>

4 -> Install new plugin

code = npm install ejs

5 -> After install run the code in terminal as

code = node app.js
